Prostomium as long as wide, anterior margin projected anteriorly, lateral margins rounded, posterior margin deeply cleft, about as long as ¼ prostomial length, reaching slightly behind posterior eyes, without longitudinal depression (
Fig. 13B
). Antennae minute, directed laterally, fusiform, blunt, twice as long as wide, 4/5 as long as interocular distance. Eyes brownish, anterior eyes as long as wide, larger than posterior rounded ones.

A recently collected non-type specimen (AM W.7439) shows a reddish hue but not a definite pigmentation pattern. This reddish pigmentation is visible in the anterior (
Fig. 14A
), and posterior regions (
Fig. 14E
), slightly less evident in the prostomium (
Fig. 14B
), and especially in the neurochaetal lobe (
Fig. 14C
).
